<paragraph blockId="158.[151,1437,254,1054]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis box="[151,235,256,281]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Leaves</emphasis>
veins raised and rectangular in cross-section adaxially; basal pinna 4.9(0.8–13.7) cm wide; apical pinna 12.6(5.7–23.2) cm wide. 
<emphasis box="[524,693,293,319]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Inflorescences</emphasis>
prophyll margins with irregular, spine-like projections; flower pits usually spirally arranged, not distantly spaced.
</paragraph>
